Description: Papyrus. Eight small disassociated fragments. Four are Greek (12, 13, 4 and 4 partial lines on one side; traces of writing on the back of three of the fragments); one demotic; one is indistinct (possibly traces of Greek) and two are uninscribed.
Curator's comments: The demotic fragment contains the word for 'regnal-year', with traces of numbers slightly above it to the right.
